      "note_no": "86",
      "note": "The term abkam signifies \"dumb\" both in the literal, physiological sense and (as in colloquial English) in the sense of being \"unable to speak properly\" on account of intellectual weakness: i.e., \"dull-witted\" or \"stupid\". Both these meanings are contained in the above Qur'anic description."
